description: A walk around the beautiful Petworth Park in Sussex. With over 700 acres of parks and gardens there's plenty to see. There are over 900 resident deer and several ancient trees to look out for on this circular tour of the 'Capability' Brown landscaped grounds. The 17th-century mansion contains galleries, fine furniture and sculptures. Just a few miles to the north of the park you will find Ebernoe Common. The national nature reserve is a nice place to extend your walk. There's woodland, streams, several ponds and lots of wildlife to see on the site.
